:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-7
* Climate can be ==affected by mountains==.
* Mountains `receive more rainfall` than low lying areas because as air is forced over the **higher ground** `it cools`,causing moist air to condense and fall out as rainfall. 
* The higher the place is `above sea level` the `colder` it will be.
* This happens because `as altitude increase` air becomes `thinner` and is `less able to absorb and retain heat`.That is why you may see ==snow on the top of mountains== all year round.
